## Database — Scale from Day 1

### Index every WHERE / JOIN / ORDER BY / GROUP BY column

```typescript
// ❌ Slow on large tables — missing index on status
const rows = await executor.select().from(jobs).where(eq(jobs.status, 'pending'));

// ✅ Covered by composite index: jobs(status, user_id, created_at)
```

### No N+1

```typescript
// ❌ N+1: 1 query + N follow-up queries
for (const job of jobs) {
  const user = await db.select().from(users).where(eq(users.id, job.userId));
}

// ✅ Batch: 2 queries total
const userIds = [...new Set(jobs.map((j) => j.userId))];
const usersMap = Object.fromEntries(
  (await db.select().from(users).where(inArray(users.id, userIds))).map((u) => [u.id, u])
);
```

### Transaction for multi-step writes

```typescript
await db.transaction(async (tx) => {
  await tx.update(credits).set({ balance: newBalance }).where(eq(credits.userId, userId));
  await tx.insert(jobs).values({ /* ... */ });
});
```

### Pagination always for list APIs

```typescript
// ✅ Cursor pagination for large data
const rows = await executor
  .select(/* specific columns */)
  .from(jobs)
  .where(and(eq(jobs.userId, userId), cursor ? gt(jobs.id, cursor) : undefined))
  .orderBy(jobs.id)
  .limit(pageSize);

// < 10k rows → offset OK
// > 10k rows → cursor pagination required
// Never load full list and slice in app — always LIMIT in SQL
```

### Drizzle: select specific columns

```typescript
// ❌
await executor.select().from(plans).where(eq(plans.payerType, 'user'));

// ✅
await executor
  .select({ id: plans.id, slug: plans.clerkSlug })
  .from(plans)
  .innerJoin(planBenefits, eq(plans.id, planBenefits.planId))
  .where(and(eq(plans.payerType, payerType), inArray(plans.clerkSlug, slugs)));
```

