## Naming

- Table/column: `snake_case` (DB) → Drizzle maps to `camelCase` (TS).
- File/export: `PascalCase` for components/classes, `camelCase` for utils.
- Types: `PascalCase`.
- Do not mix `userId`, `user_id`, `uid` in the same context.

---

## Comments

- **Comments in code**: English (see `documentation-language.mdc`).
- Write **intent**, not mechanics. Don't restate the code.
- JSDoc: only when the purpose isn't obvious from the signature.

```typescript
/**
 * Resolve plan slugs from Clerk webhook line items.
 * Falls back to clerk_plan_id lookup if slug is missing (edge case on first sync).
 * @param executor - DB or transaction for composability.
 * @param items - Line items from subscription/payment webhook.
 */
```

---

## When to Create a New File

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Logic used in 1 place | Add to nearest existing file |
| Logic shared across 2–3 places in same feature | `constants.ts` of that feature |
| Logic shared across features | `src/libs/` or `src/constants/` |
| Type used across layers | `src/types/<feature>/` |
| DB enum | `models/Schema.ts` (pgEnum) |
| Server DB access | `src/libs/persistence/<feature>/` |
| Browser HTTP call | `src/libs/apis/<feature>/` |

**Never scatter** `types.ts`, `enums.ts`, `utils.ts` across the project. See `.cursor/rules/coding-organization.mdc`.

